The binding affinity between different tubulin isotypes and TauR2 was explored by performing relative binding energy calculation similar to earlier studies67–69. The stable region of the trajectory observed in between 70 ns to 100 ns and hence we extracted 70–100 ns trajectory to perform the binding energy calculations for all the tubulin-TauR2 complexes. The tool ‘g_mmpbsa’ v1.6 was used to calculate binding energy using MM/PBSA approach70 implemented in gromacs 2018.1. The parameters for binding energy calculations were taken from the earlier similar studies59,69,71–73. The binding energy (ΔGbind) of tubulin and TauR2 was calculated by using the following Eq. (1),1\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
